1
00:00:03,044 --> 00:00:06,134
{\an8}<i>♪ The Simpsons ♪</i>

2
00:00:09,509 --> 00:00:10,759
D'oh!

3
00:00:10,844 --> 00:00:12,354
-Ahh!
-(tires screeching)

4
00:00:15,223 --> 00:00:16,143
(Homer screaming)

5
00:00:28,236 --> 00:00:30,316
{\an8}Uh, why do they have
to put all this crud

6
00:00:30,405 --> 00:00:31,815
{\an8}in my newspaper?

7
00:00:31,906 --> 00:00:35,786
{\an8}"World," "The Arts,"
"Religion."

8
00:00:35,869 --> 00:00:37,659
{\an8}A-ha! Here it is.

9
00:00:37,746 --> 00:00:38,906
{\an8}"Kickin' Back!"

10
00:00:40,540 --> 00:00:42,540
{\an8}Hey, who cut something
out of my paper?

11
00:00:42,625 --> 00:00:43,955
{\an8}Not me.

12
00:00:44,044 --> 00:00:45,634
{\an8}Not me. I'm more
of a mail-tamperer.

13
00:00:45,712 --> 00:00:47,342
{\an8}Well, don't look at me,

14
00:00:47,422 --> 00:00:48,512
{\an8}just because I'm holding
a pair of scissors.

15
00:00:49,883 --> 00:00:52,843
{\an8}Scissors, which I need
to, uh, to...

16
00:00:52,927 --> 00:00:55,557
{\an8}gussy up these curtains.

17
00:00:57,974 --> 00:00:59,354
{\an8}(rings)

18
00:00:59,434 --> 00:01:00,354
{\an8}Hello.

19
00:01:00,435 --> 00:01:01,895
{\an8}Oh, hi, Lenny.

20
00:01:01,978 --> 00:01:04,688
{\an8}No, why would I need
a ride this afternoon?

21
00:01:04,773 --> 00:01:06,903
{\an8}(noisy vacuuming)

22
00:01:06,983 --> 00:01:09,073
{\an8}Where?!

23
00:01:09,152 --> 00:01:11,532
{\an8}To the big annual what?!

24
00:01:12,906 --> 00:01:15,026
{\an8}Lenny? Aw, well,
if it was big and annual

25
00:01:15,116 --> 00:01:18,036
{\an8}I'm sure they'd have
mentioned it in the newspaper.

26
00:01:18,119 --> 00:01:19,749
(dog growling)

27
00:01:19,829 --> 00:01:24,499
{\an8}Yeah, it's a lazy,
dog-dangling afternoon.

28
00:01:24,584 --> 00:01:28,054
{\an8}But something's
a little off.

29
00:01:28,129 --> 00:01:30,089
{\an8}Hey, Marge, you don't smoke.

30
00:01:30,173 --> 00:01:32,513
{\an8}Well, I just felt
like filling the house

31
00:01:32,592 --> 00:01:35,512
{\an8}with the rich,
satisfying smell of tobacco.

32
00:01:35,595 --> 00:01:36,505
(coughs)

33
00:01:37,680 --> 00:01:38,640
(whistles)

34
00:01:38,723 --> 00:01:40,063
{\an8}You're nuts.

35
00:01:40,141 --> 00:01:41,181
{\an8}I got to get some fresh air.

36
00:01:43,186 --> 00:01:44,936
{\an8}-No, Homie, wait.
-What's wrong with you?

37
00:01:45,021 --> 00:01:46,861
{\an8}What are you trying
to hide from me?

38
00:01:46,940 --> 00:01:48,570
{\an8}(sniffing)
What's that smell?

39
00:01:48,650 --> 00:01:53,110
{\an8}Onions... chili powder...
cumin... juicy ground chuck!

40
00:01:53,196 --> 00:01:54,856
It's chili! Oh, my God!

41
00:01:54,948 --> 00:01:56,618
I'm missing the chili cook-off!

42
00:01:56,699 --> 00:01:58,489
I'm missing the cook-off.

43
00:01:58,576 --> 00:02:00,196
It's going on right now
and I'm missing it.

44
00:02:00,286 --> 00:02:02,656
All right, I was trying
to keep it from you,

45
00:02:02,747 --> 00:02:05,077
but I had a good reason.

46
00:02:05,166 --> 00:02:06,496
Every time you go
to that cook-off

47
00:02:06,584 --> 00:02:08,214
you get drunk
as a poet on payday.

48
00:02:08,294 --> 00:02:09,554
Remember last year?

49
00:02:10,922 --> 00:02:12,842
Look at me.

50
00:02:12,924 --> 00:02:16,804
I'm a puffy pink cloud.

51
00:02:16,886 --> 00:02:19,136
Yee-hee-hee-ha-ha!

52
00:02:19,222 --> 00:02:20,432
Oh!

53
00:02:20,515 --> 00:02:21,845
Oh, well, of course

54
00:02:21,933 --> 00:02:24,643
everything looks bad
if you remember it.

55
00:02:24,727 --> 00:02:26,767
Now, where are
my chili boots?

56
00:02:26,855 --> 00:02:28,305
Ah!

57
00:02:28,398 --> 00:02:30,478
(grunting)

58
00:02:30,567 --> 00:02:33,487
Okay, we'll go
to the chili cook-off.

59
00:02:33,570 --> 00:02:36,070
But I want you to promise me
you won't have any beer.

60
00:02:36,156 --> 00:02:38,696
Okay, quit nagging me.
I won't have any beer.

61
00:02:38,783 --> 00:02:40,663
Geez, why don't you have
a cigarette or something?

62
00:02:40,743 --> 00:02:43,713
Mm, I suppose I could.

63
00:02:49,377 --> 00:02:51,877
I'm gonna go get
some vegetarian chili

64
00:02:51,963 --> 00:02:53,673
before they get desperate
and add meat.

65
00:02:53,756 --> 00:02:54,876
I'm gonna go
claim some valuables

66
00:02:54,966 --> 00:02:56,256
at the lost and found.

67
00:02:56,342 --> 00:02:59,552
Ooh, look at that
adorable spice rack.

68
00:02:59,637 --> 00:03:01,507
Eight spices?

69
00:03:01,598 --> 00:03:03,518
Oh, some must be doubles.

70
00:03:03,600 --> 00:03:05,940
"Oregano"?
What the hell...

71
00:03:06,019 --> 00:03:08,729
Marge, we're
missing the chili.

72
00:03:08,813 --> 00:03:10,773
Less artsy, more fartsy.

73
00:03:10,857 --> 00:03:12,777
Homer, I happen
to like handicrafts

74
00:03:12,859 --> 00:03:14,899
much more than
stuffing my face.

75
00:03:14,986 --> 00:03:16,606
Fine. I'll come find you

76
00:03:16,696 --> 00:03:18,566
when I'm ready
to stop having fun.

77
00:03:18,656 --> 00:03:21,156
Remember your promise--
no drinking.

78
00:03:23,077 --> 00:03:25,037
Stupor pooper.

79
00:03:25,121 --> 00:03:29,331
♪♪ (country)

80
00:03:29,417 --> 00:03:31,337
Howdy, howdy,
Marge and Hom--

81
00:03:31,419 --> 00:03:32,959
Oh, my mistake.

82
00:03:33,046 --> 00:03:34,586
Homer's not even with you.

83
00:03:34,672 --> 00:03:38,432
Probably just knocking back
a few "refreshments."

84
00:03:38,509 --> 00:03:40,389
Thank you for your
concern, Helen.

85
00:03:40,470 --> 00:03:42,060
Homer isn't drinking today.

86
00:03:42,138 --> 00:03:44,678
Oh, I think it's lovely
that he said that

87
00:03:44,766 --> 00:03:46,636
and that you believed him.

88
00:03:46,726 --> 00:03:50,146
Now, Helen, let us not glory
in Homer's binge-drinking.

89
00:03:50,230 --> 00:03:53,900
There but for the grace of God
goes Marge herself.

90
00:04:07,038 --> 00:04:08,328
Ooh, man, he's here--

91
00:04:08,414 --> 00:04:11,004
The dude with
the fireproof stomach.

92
00:04:13,086 --> 00:04:15,626
CROWD (gasping): Whoa!
Spoon! Spoon! Spoon!

93
00:04:15,713 --> 00:04:18,263
They say he
carved it himself

94
00:04:18,341 --> 00:04:19,761
from a bigger spoon.

95
00:04:23,513 --> 00:04:24,893
Five-alarm chili, eh?

96
00:04:24,973 --> 00:04:27,183
Mm-hmm.

97
00:04:27,267 --> 00:04:30,137
One... two...

98
00:04:30,228 --> 00:04:32,438
Hey, what's the big idea?

99
00:04:32,522 --> 00:04:34,022
Oh, I admit it.

100
00:04:34,107 --> 00:04:36,857
It's only two-alarm,
two-and-a-half, tops.

101
00:04:36,943 --> 00:04:39,863
I just wanted to be a big man
in front of the kids.

102
00:04:39,946 --> 00:04:42,616
Daddy, are you
going to jail?

103
00:04:42,699 --> 00:04:45,199
We'll see, son.
We'll see.

104
00:04:49,956 --> 00:04:51,746
Evenin', little lady.

105
00:04:51,833 --> 00:04:54,753
Do you reckon a square
could get a dance?

106
00:04:54,836 --> 00:04:57,416
Oh... it looks so complicated.

107
00:04:57,505 --> 00:04:59,375
Do you know how?

108
00:04:59,465 --> 00:05:03,885
Ma'am, I wouldn't honk the honk
if I couldn't tonk the tonk.

109
00:05:07,056 --> 00:05:08,176
Woo-woo!

110
00:05:11,269 --> 00:05:12,189
Hmm.

111
00:05:12,270 --> 00:05:14,270
A bland, timid entry

112
00:05:14,355 --> 00:05:17,185
suitable, perhaps, for patients
recovering from surgery.

113
00:05:18,943 --> 00:05:21,033
WIGGUM: That Simpson,

114
00:05:21,112 --> 00:05:23,412
he thinks he's
the pope of chili town.

115
00:05:23,489 --> 00:05:26,449
Well, this year
I am ready for him.

116
00:05:30,246 --> 00:05:33,666
HOMER: Hello, Chief.

117
00:05:35,293 --> 00:05:36,673
Afternoon, Homer.

118
00:05:36,753 --> 00:05:38,883
Care for some chili?

119
00:05:38,963 --> 00:05:43,183
I've added an extra ingredient
just for you--

120
00:05:43,259 --> 00:05:47,009
The merciless peppers
of Quetzlzacatenango!

121
00:05:47,096 --> 00:05:48,256
(crowd gasps)

122
00:05:48,348 --> 00:05:52,138
Grown deep
in the jungle primeval

123
00:05:52,226 --> 00:05:56,396
by the inmates of
a Guatemalan insane asylum.

124
00:05:57,982 --> 00:06:00,282
Uh, Wiggy?
My chili's getting cold.

125
00:06:03,446 --> 00:06:04,486
(gasping)

126
00:06:07,450 --> 00:06:08,910
(sizzling)

127
00:06:08,993 --> 00:06:10,293
(screaming)

128
00:06:12,538 --> 00:06:14,828
Hot! Hot! Hot! Hot!

129
00:06:18,628 --> 00:06:19,628
D'oh!

130
00:06:19,712 --> 00:06:21,632
Oh, my tongue is burning up!

131
00:06:21,714 --> 00:06:23,264
Beer! Baby needs a beer!

132
00:06:23,341 --> 00:06:24,761
Homer!

133
00:06:24,842 --> 00:06:26,642
You promised you wouldn't drink.

134
00:06:26,719 --> 00:06:28,849
But I need it!

135
00:06:31,766 --> 00:06:33,176
Yeah.

136
00:06:33,267 --> 00:06:34,687
Oh, lousy Wiggum.

137
00:06:34,769 --> 00:06:37,729
Now the whole town
thinks I'm a chili wuss.

138
00:06:37,814 --> 00:06:40,614
Wait, Mister.
You're drinking a candle.

139
00:06:40,691 --> 00:06:43,901
You don't want to get wax
in your mouth, do you?

140
00:06:43,986 --> 00:06:45,986
Maybe I do, son.

141
00:06:46,072 --> 00:06:48,742
Maybe I do.

142
00:06:51,244 --> 00:06:53,164
(gags)

143
00:06:53,246 --> 00:06:54,996
Outstanding.

144
00:06:56,707 --> 00:06:58,877
Hey, everybody,
look who's back.

145
00:06:58,960 --> 00:07:02,420
It's the big baby!

146
00:07:02,505 --> 00:07:04,375
Oh, this porridge is too hot.

147
00:07:04,465 --> 00:07:05,625
Oh, waa-waa-waa!

148
00:07:05,716 --> 00:07:07,086
(laughing)

149
00:07:07,176 --> 00:07:08,586
Want some more, do you?

150
00:07:08,678 --> 00:07:10,968
Well, sure.
Heck, it's not my job

151
00:07:11,055 --> 00:07:13,135
to talk people out of
killing themselves.

152
00:07:13,224 --> 00:07:16,064
Ah...

153
00:07:16,144 --> 00:07:17,104
(gasps)

154
00:07:17,186 --> 00:07:18,726
(murmuring)

155
00:07:18,813 --> 00:07:20,823
More, please.

156
00:07:22,733 --> 00:07:26,033
(gulping)

157
00:07:26,112 --> 00:07:27,612
Good Lord,
this can't be happening.

158
00:07:27,697 --> 00:07:29,237
By all medical logic

159
00:07:29,323 --> 00:07:31,243
steam should be shooting
out of his ears.

160
00:07:31,325 --> 00:07:32,535
His ears if we're lucky.

161
00:07:35,079 --> 00:07:39,789
Well, Chief,
don't quit your day job--

162
00:07:39,876 --> 00:07:42,836
(chuckles)
whatever that is.

163
00:07:42,920 --> 00:07:45,970
(laughter, applause)

164
00:07:46,048 --> 00:07:48,428
Heh-heh.
My finest hour...

165
00:07:48,509 --> 00:07:50,969
and Marge wasn't
even here to see it.

166
00:07:51,053 --> 00:07:55,393
(rumbling)

167
00:07:55,475 --> 00:07:59,145
Ooh, I don't feel so good.

168
00:07:59,228 --> 00:08:01,108
(groaning)

169
00:08:03,232 --> 00:08:06,442
Flanders,
you've got to help me.

170
00:08:06,527 --> 00:08:08,447
Sure, buddy.
I'd be happy to help out.

171
00:08:08,529 --> 00:08:10,199
What can I do... diddly do...

172
00:08:10,281 --> 00:08:13,781
diddily-doodily-diddily-hoobily-
hobbily-hibbily-gooble-gobble...

173
00:08:13,868 --> 00:08:15,238
gooble gabba-gabba-hey?

174
00:08:15,328 --> 00:08:16,248
(gasps)

175
00:08:19,707 --> 00:08:20,877
Huh?

176
00:08:20,958 --> 00:08:23,288
Goo-goo-ga-joob?

177
00:08:23,377 --> 00:08:24,707
Haw! Haw!

178
00:08:24,795 --> 00:08:26,295
Haw haw!

179
00:08:26,380 --> 00:08:30,090
(waa-waa trumpet sound)

180
00:08:30,176 --> 00:08:32,046
(distorted belch)

181
00:08:34,138 --> 00:08:35,428
(screams)

182
00:08:37,350 --> 00:08:39,100
Mister, do you
need some help?

183
00:08:39,185 --> 00:08:40,725
Let him go, Ralph.

184
00:08:40,811 --> 00:08:41,851
He knows what he's doing.

185
00:08:41,938 --> 00:08:44,608
(wailing)

186
00:08:50,154 --> 00:08:52,034
(panting)

187
00:08:56,035 --> 00:08:57,245
What's happening to me?

188
00:08:57,328 --> 00:08:58,828
Okay, retrace your steps.

189
00:08:58,913 --> 00:09:01,673
Woke up,
fought with Marge,

190
00:09:01,749 --> 00:09:04,419
ate Guatemalan
insanity peppers.

191
00:09:04,502 --> 00:09:08,052
Then I-- Ohh.

192
00:09:08,130 --> 00:09:10,220
Where am I? Shelbyville?

193
00:09:10,299 --> 00:09:11,679
(screams)

194
00:09:13,928 --> 00:09:15,258
Man, this is crazy.

195
00:09:15,346 --> 00:09:17,806
I hope I didn't brain my damage.

196
00:09:17,890 --> 00:09:19,680
I better check my pupils.

197
00:09:27,733 --> 00:09:29,613
(hissing)

198
00:09:30,653 --> 00:09:34,073
Oh... kay.

199
00:09:34,156 --> 00:09:37,196
I think I'm gonna be
leaving now.

200
00:09:42,665 --> 00:09:44,125
Huh?

201
00:09:48,296 --> 00:09:50,626
Sunrise, sunset...

202
00:09:50,715 --> 00:09:52,795
Sunrise, sunset...

203
00:09:52,883 --> 00:09:55,303
Sunrise, sunset,
sunrise, sunset,

204
00:09:55,386 --> 00:09:56,926
sunrise, sunset, sunrise...

205
00:09:57,013 --> 00:09:58,393
(screams)

206
00:09:58,472 --> 00:10:02,352
Note to self:
Stop doing anything.

207
00:10:04,103 --> 00:10:06,613
Has anyone seen Homer?

208
00:10:06,689 --> 00:10:08,189
Marge, better
you hear it from me

209
00:10:08,274 --> 00:10:09,944
than some gossipy neighbor.

210
00:10:10,026 --> 00:10:11,936
Homer made a total
jackass of himself.

211
00:10:12,028 --> 00:10:14,778
Oh, Helen, that's enough.
Call off your dogs.

212
00:10:14,864 --> 00:10:16,744
But someone had
to tell her.

213
00:10:16,824 --> 00:10:18,124
And I got here first.

214
00:10:18,200 --> 00:10:20,700
-Helen, zip it.
-Oh please. Tim.

215
00:10:20,786 --> 00:10:22,956
Zip it. Ziparoo.

216
00:10:23,039 --> 00:10:24,249
No beer, huh?

217
00:10:24,332 --> 00:10:25,962
(grumbling)

218
00:10:26,042 --> 00:10:29,842
I guess I know what a promise
from Homer J. Simpson is worth.

219
00:10:35,843 --> 00:10:38,643
Hey, buddy, get back there
with the other rocks.

220
00:10:39,972 --> 00:10:41,102
Huh?

221
00:10:41,182 --> 00:10:42,812
A tortoise?

222
00:10:42,892 --> 00:10:45,192
"Follow... the..."

223
00:10:45,269 --> 00:10:47,359
(gasps)
This must be why I'm here!

224
00:10:47,438 --> 00:10:49,398
Follow the what?
Follow the what?

225
00:10:49,482 --> 00:10:51,402
Hurry up!

226
00:10:54,487 --> 00:10:55,987
Get moving you stupid--

227
00:10:56,072 --> 00:10:59,872
When I'm kicking you,
that means hurry up.

228
00:10:59,950 --> 00:11:01,950
Come on.

229
00:11:15,132 --> 00:11:17,052
Oh, you want me
to climb that, huh?

230
00:11:17,134 --> 00:11:19,144
No problemo.

231
00:11:19,220 --> 00:11:21,100
(rumbling)

232
00:11:23,099 --> 00:11:24,729
Oh!

233
00:11:24,809 --> 00:11:26,809
This is 'cause I kicked you,
isn't it?

234
00:11:29,355 --> 00:11:30,515
(grunting)

235
00:11:32,525 --> 00:11:33,975
Lis, check it out.

236
00:11:35,152 --> 00:11:36,322
I saw it, Bart.

237
00:11:36,404 --> 00:11:37,864
You're just mad

238
00:11:37,947 --> 00:11:38,907
'cause there's
no clock in your hat.

239
00:11:38,989 --> 00:11:40,489
What hat?

240
00:11:40,574 --> 00:11:43,294
Ah, this baby's wasted
on an idiot like you.

241
00:11:43,369 --> 00:11:44,909
Where's Homer?

242
00:11:44,995 --> 00:11:46,365
Your father decided
that he'd rather come home

243
00:11:46,455 --> 00:11:49,375
in a taxi... or a police car.

244
00:11:49,458 --> 00:11:51,338
(grunting)

245
00:11:53,629 --> 00:11:55,339
(gasping)

246
00:11:55,423 --> 00:11:57,303
Marge, thank God
you're here.

247
00:11:57,383 --> 00:11:58,473
Where's the car?

248
00:11:58,551 --> 00:12:01,971
Marge? Marge?

249
00:12:02,054 --> 00:12:03,644
Oh, now what?

250
00:12:03,723 --> 00:12:07,143
If you're still mad at me,
I'm gonna be really mad.

251
00:12:07,226 --> 00:12:08,636
Come on, Marge,
will you..?

252
00:12:08,728 --> 00:12:11,478
Fight fair.
I never do this to you.

253
00:12:11,564 --> 00:12:13,114
Talk to me!

254
00:12:13,190 --> 00:12:16,070
(wind blowing)

255
00:12:20,531 --> 00:12:23,831
Oh, I hate this place.

256
00:12:23,909 --> 00:12:25,749
Why am I here?

257
00:12:25,828 --> 00:12:28,208
VOICE: <i>You are on</i>
<i>a quest for knowledge.</i>

258
00:12:28,289 --> 00:12:29,169
Who said that?

259
00:12:39,049 --> 00:12:40,469
Fear not, Homer.

260
00:12:40,551 --> 00:12:42,141
I am your spirit guide.

261
00:12:42,219 --> 00:12:43,299
Hiya.

262
00:12:43,387 --> 00:12:45,307
There is a lesson
you must learn.

263
00:12:45,389 --> 00:12:47,729
If it's about laying off
the insanity peppers

264
00:12:47,808 --> 00:12:48,768
I'm way ahead of you.

265
00:12:48,851 --> 00:12:51,021
No, I speak of a deeper wisdom.

266
00:12:51,103 --> 00:12:53,023
The problem, Homer,

267
00:12:53,105 --> 00:12:55,355
is that the mind is
always chattering away

268
00:12:55,441 --> 00:12:57,651
with a thousand thoughts
at once.

269
00:12:57,735 --> 00:12:59,855
Yeah, that's me all right.

270
00:12:59,945 --> 00:13:01,815
(wind blowing)

271
00:13:03,324 --> 00:13:06,164
Clarity is the path
to inner peace.

272
00:13:06,243 --> 00:13:08,453
Well, what should I do?
Should I meditate?

273
00:13:08,537 --> 00:13:10,747
Should I get rid
of all my possessions?

274
00:13:10,831 --> 00:13:13,131
Are you kidding?!
(chuckles)

275
00:13:13,209 --> 00:13:15,499
If anything, you should
get more possessions.

276
00:13:15,586 --> 00:13:17,296
You don't even have
a computer.

277
00:13:17,379 --> 00:13:20,929
You know, I have been meaning
to take a spiritual journey

278
00:13:21,008 --> 00:13:22,298
and I--

279
00:13:22,384 --> 00:13:23,724
(growling)

280
00:13:23,803 --> 00:13:25,683
Hey, knock it off!

281
00:13:25,763 --> 00:13:27,603
Sorry.

282
00:13:27,681 --> 00:13:29,351
I am a coyote.

283
00:13:29,433 --> 00:13:31,023
Look, just give me
some inner peace

284
00:13:31,101 --> 00:13:32,521
or I'll mop the floor
with you.

285
00:13:32,603 --> 00:13:35,563
Good. Your mind is in
a state of readiness.

286
00:13:35,648 --> 00:13:37,318
So listen well.

287
00:13:37,399 --> 00:13:39,819
To make yourself complete,

288
00:13:39,902 --> 00:13:41,492
