289
00:13:41,570 --> 00:13:42,990
Soul mate?

290
00:13:43,072 --> 00:13:45,242
Your kindred spirit.

291
00:13:45,324 --> 00:13:47,704
The one with whom you share
an unspoken bond,

292
00:13:47,785 --> 00:13:50,495
a profound mystical
understanding.

293
00:13:50,579 --> 00:13:52,409
That's it?

294
00:13:52,498 --> 00:13:54,328
Well, that's Marge.
Big deal.

295
00:13:54,416 --> 00:13:57,166
Great spiritual quest,
Wolfie.

296
00:13:57,253 --> 00:13:59,513
My soul mate is Marge.

297
00:13:59,588 --> 00:14:01,258
Is it?

298
00:14:07,388 --> 00:14:09,808
Hey wait. Come back.

299
00:14:09,890 --> 00:14:11,060
Oh.

300
00:14:11,141 --> 00:14:12,851
(horn blowing)

301
00:14:12,935 --> 00:14:14,265
Oh! A ghost train!

302
00:14:14,353 --> 00:14:16,403
And so little time
to get out of the way.

303
00:14:16,480 --> 00:14:17,440
Now less...

304
00:14:17,523 --> 00:14:19,113
Now none!
(screams)

305
00:14:19,191 --> 00:14:20,441
D'oh!

306
00:14:21,652 --> 00:14:24,662
Hey, get off the course,
you bum!

307
00:14:24,738 --> 00:14:26,158
Security.

308
00:14:26,240 --> 00:14:27,530
(whistle blowing)

309
00:14:27,616 --> 00:14:30,116
Wha-- Golf course?

310
00:14:30,202 --> 00:14:32,752
Did I dream that whole thing?

311
00:14:32,830 --> 00:14:35,830
Maybe the desert
was just a sand trap.

312
00:14:35,916 --> 00:14:37,286
Oh, and I bet

313
00:14:37,376 --> 00:14:40,956
that crazy pyramid
was just the Pro Shop.

314
00:14:41,046 --> 00:14:44,166
And that talking coyote
was really just a talking dog.

315
00:14:44,258 --> 00:14:45,628
Hi, Homer.
Find your soul mate.

316
00:14:45,718 --> 00:14:47,138
Hey, wait a minute.

317
00:14:47,219 --> 00:14:49,429
There's no such thing
as a talking dog.

318
00:14:49,513 --> 00:14:50,853
(barking)

319
00:14:50,931 --> 00:14:52,271
Damn straight.

320
00:14:52,349 --> 00:14:54,059
So then I says to Mabel,
I says--

321
00:14:54,143 --> 00:14:55,233
Hi, kids.

322
00:14:55,311 --> 00:14:56,481
I'll finish this later.
Hi Dad.

323
00:14:56,562 --> 00:14:58,732
-Where is your mother?
-Out back.

324
00:14:58,814 --> 00:15:00,904
So anyway,
I says to Mabel, I says--

325
00:15:00,983 --> 00:15:02,033
Hi, honey.

326
00:15:03,611 --> 00:15:06,951
(singsongy)
Oh, I guess you're cranky

327
00:15:07,031 --> 00:15:09,451
because I didn't
come home last night.

328
00:15:09,533 --> 00:15:12,453
I'm "cranky" because
my husband got drunk

329
00:15:12,536 --> 00:15:15,406
and humiliated me
in front of the entire town.

330
00:15:15,497 --> 00:15:18,327
You broke
your promise, Homer.

331
00:15:18,417 --> 00:15:20,417
Oh, honey,
I didn't get drunk.

332
00:15:20,502 --> 00:15:23,052
I just went to a strange
fantasy world.

333
00:15:23,130 --> 00:15:24,970
Come on, you got
to believe me.

334
00:15:25,049 --> 00:15:26,219
You're my soul mate.

335
00:15:26,300 --> 00:15:28,260
Don't "soul mate" me!

336
00:15:28,344 --> 00:15:29,894
Okay.

337
00:15:29,970 --> 00:15:31,890
(snoring)

338
00:15:31,972 --> 00:15:35,682
That coyote said my soul mate
would understand me

339
00:15:35,768 --> 00:15:38,148
but Marge doesn't understand me
at all.

340
00:15:38,228 --> 00:15:39,858
Maybe we're not kindred spirits.

341
00:15:41,357 --> 00:15:43,857
We don't have
anything in common.

342
00:15:43,943 --> 00:15:46,493
Look at these records.

343
00:15:46,570 --> 00:15:49,660
Jim Nabors, Glen Campbell,
The Doodletown Pipers.

344
00:15:49,740 --> 00:15:51,530
Now look at her records.

345
00:15:51,617 --> 00:15:53,447
They stink!

346
00:15:53,535 --> 00:15:57,035
Oh. Maybe I had
that crazy dream for a reason.

347
00:15:59,375 --> 00:16:03,165
Wherever my soul mate is,
it's not here.

348
00:16:11,845 --> 00:16:14,715
